The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 December is 132,038 (15,218.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 December, there were 6,506 new confirmed cases (749.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 December, there were 5,422 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 20% (1,084 extra cases).
